3. What are intermediate and terminal operater in stream
==========================================================
Intermediate Operations
These operations transform a Stream into another Stream.
They are lazy—they don't execute until a terminal operation is invoked.
Multiple intermediate operations can be chained together.
Examples:
filter(): Filters elements based on a condition.
map(): Transforms each element.
sorted(): Sorts elements.
distinct(): Removes duplicates.

Terminal Operations
These operations produce a result from the Stream (e.g., a collection, a value, or a side effect).
They trigger the execution of intermediate operations.
Examples:
forEach(): Performs an action on each element.
collect(): Converts Stream into a collection (e.g., List, Set).
reduce(): Reduces elements to a single result.
count(): Counts the number of elements.

